08/12/2004
MOSCOW, Russia -- Greek Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis kicked off a three-day visit to Russia on Tuesday (7 December).
On Wednesday, he held talks with President Vladimir Putin.
Two agreements were to be sealed between the two delegations -- one on enhancing political and economic ties, and another on fighting terrorism.
(Kathimerini, ANA - 08/12/04;
MPA - 07/12/04)
